# Plan — solo-law
Status: READY (all 6 research questions answered and integrated below)

---

## Demo Concept
**Solo Law Premium Website + Integrated Multilingual CMS + Agentic Browser-GPU AI Content Assistant**

Full Angular + Flask app. Public-facing law firm site (editorial, institutional) driven 100% from CMS backend. CMS panel lets editor manage practice areas, publications, brand assets across 2 locales. Hero feature: in-browser WebLLM/WebGPU agentic loop (draft → reflection → rubric-eval → emit/loop) embedded in CMS for copy drafting and translation. Richness: 10/10.

---

## Architecture

### Frontend — Angular 18+ + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS
Build: `ng build --base-href /demos/solo-law/` → dist copied to `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/solo-law/`

**Public routes:**
- `/` — Hero (cinematic, large editorial imagery, firm name, tagline)
- `/practice-areas` — Grid/list of all practice areas (locale-driven)
- `/practice-areas/:slug` — Individual practice area (editorial layout, related publications)
- `/publications` — Publications index (filterable by practice area, date)
- `/publications/:slug` — Article page (editorial typography, refined layout)
- `/contact` — Minimal contact form (static)

**CMS routes (JWT-protected):**
- `/cms/login` — Editor login
- `/cms/dashboard` — Overview cards (counts, recent edits)
- `/cms/practice-areas` — CRUD list
- `/cms/practice-areas/edit/:id` — Form with AI Assist panel
- `/cms/publications` — CRUD list
- `/cms/publications/edit/:id` — Form with AI Assist panel
- `/cms/brand-assets` — Asset library, palette display
- `/cms/i18n` — Translation manager (side-by-side EN/ES)

**Key Angular services:**
1. `ApiService` — HTTP client to `/solo-law/...` Flask endpoints; attaches JWT
2. `AuthService` — Login, token storage, route guards
3. `AiAgentService` — WebLLM/WebGPU agentic controller (see AI section)
4. `I18nService` — wraps `@ngx-translate/core` v18 (Signal-native, `provideTranslateService` + `HttpLoader`); UI strings from `assets/i18n/{en,es,fr}.json`; content (practice areas, publications) fetched per-locale via backend API; runtime switch via `translateService.use(lang)` (no reload)
5. `ContentService` — CRUD wrappers for practice areas, publications, assets

**Locale switcher:** Header component with EN / ES toggle; on switch, re-fetches all content for new locale.

---

### Backend — Flask Blueprint (solo_law_blueprint.py, Python OOP)

Registers at prefix `/solo-law` in `mw-backend/server.py`. SQLite WAL mode. All Python OOP.

**Python OOP class map:**
```
SoloLawDB          — db init, WAL pragma, connection pool
PracticeAreaModel  — CRUD, multilingual (locale field)
PublicationModel   — CRUD, multilingual, practice-area FK
BrandAssetModel    — CRUD, tags
ContentBlockModel  — reusable blocks (type, json_data, locale)
UserModel          — login only (re-uses existing JWT pattern from mw-backend)
SeedManager        — idempotent seed on first run
```

**Database schema:**
```sql
-- practice_areas
id, slug, locale(en|es), title, tagline, body_html, icon_emoji, hero_image_url, display_order, published, updated_at

-- publications
id, slug, locale(en|es), title, excerpt, body_html, author, practice_area_id, published_at, published, updated_at

-- brand_assets
id, name, type(color|font|image|logo), value, tag, created_at

-- content_blocks
id, block_type, locale, json_data, ref_id, ref_type, created_at

-- cms_users
id, email, password_hash, role(editor|admin), created_at
```

**API endpoints:**
```
GET  /solo-law/health
POST /solo-law/auth/login                    → {token, user}
GET  /solo-law/practice-areas?locale=en      → [{id,slug,title,tagline,icon,...}]
GET  /solo-law/practice-areas/:slug?locale=en → {full fields + publications[]}
POST /solo-law/cms/practice-areas            [auth] → create
PUT  /solo-law/cms/practice-areas/:id        [auth] → update
DELETE /solo-law/cms/practice-areas/:id      [auth] → delete
GET  /solo-law/publications?locale=en&practice_area=&page=1
GET  /solo-law/publications/:slug?locale=en
POST /solo-law/cms/publications              [auth]
PUT  /solo-law/cms/publications/:id          [auth]
DELETE /solo-law/cms/publications/:id        [auth]
GET  /solo-law/brand-assets
POST /solo-law/cms/brand-assets              [auth]
DELETE /solo-law/cms/brand-assets/:id        [auth]
GET  /solo-law/i18n?locale=en                → {ui_strings: {nav_home, nav_practice_areas,...}}
POST /solo-law/cms/i18n                      [auth] → upsert UI string
```

**Seed data (idempotent, English + Spanish):**

Practice areas:
1. Corporate Transactions / Transacciones Corporativas
2. Commercial Litigation / Litigación Comercial
3. Intellectual Property / Propiedad Intelectual
4. Regulatory & Compliance / Regulatorio y Cumplimiento

Publications: 5 bilingual articles (1 per practice area + 1 general), realistic legal-thought-leadership copy.

CMS credentials: `editor@soloaw.demo` / `Demo2026!` (seeded in cms_users, hashed with bcrypt)

---

### AI Engine — Agentic Browser-GPU Content Assistant

**Library:** `@mlc-ai/web-llm` v0.2.84 (chosen over transformers.js — OpenAI-compatible chat API maps cleanly to multi-turn agentic loop; native streaming; WebWorkerMLCEngine keeps Angular UI thread free).

**CDN import (ESM, no bundler required):**
```js
import * as webllm from "https://esm.run/@mlc-ai/web-llm";
```

**Primary model:** `Phi-3.5-mini-instruct-q4f16_1-MLC` (~3GB VRAM, discrete GPU)
**Fallback model:** `Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC` (~0.8GB VRAM, integrated GPU)

**Initialization pattern:**
```ts
const engine = new webllm.WebWorkerMLCEngine('/webllm-worker.js');
await engine.reload(modelId, { initProgressCallback: (r) => { /* progress bar */ } });
const reply = await engine.chat.completions.create({ messages, stream: true });
```

**Detection + fallback:**
```typescript
const gpu = await navigator.gpu?.requestAdapter();
if (!gpu) { this.mode = 'mock'; return; }
// else load WebLLM engine
```
Mock mode: returns template-fill placeholder text with [AI UNAVAILABLE — WebGPU not detected] prefix. Non-blocking.

**Agentic controller — AiAgentService:**
```
1. DRAFT   — system prompt = firm voice + practice-area context + task (draft|translate|refine)
              user prompt  = editor's instruction
              → raw draft text

2. REFLECT — system prompt = "You are a senior legal editor. Critique this draft..."
              user prompt  = {draft, task, target_locale if translation}
              → critique JSON: {issues: string[], suggestions: string[]}

3. EVAL    — system prompt = rubric evaluator
              user prompt  = {draft, critique, rubric}
              rubric axes: legal_tone (0-10), relevance (0-10), factual_grounding (0-10),
                           multilingual_correctness (0-10, if translate), brevity (0-10)
              → {scores: {...}, overall: number, pass: boolean, reason: string}

4. DECIDE  — if overall >= 7.0 OR iterations >= 2: emit final
              else: refine (feed critique back, re-draft, loop from step 1)
```

**CMS integration:** AI Assist panel slides in on right side of CMS edit form. Controls: Task selector (Draft / Translate EN→ES / Translate ES→EN / Refine), instruction textarea, Generate button. Shows streaming-like output with step indicators (Drafting... Reflecting... Evaluating... Done ✓). Editor can Accept (inserts into body field) or Dismiss.

**Smart prompting:** Brand voice context injected from brand_assets table (tone keywords, forbidden terms). Practice-area context injected from current form values.

