## Build Sequence for Demo-Builder

1. Scaffold Angular project, configure Tailwind, set base-href
2. Build Flask blueprint + SQLite schema + seed data; push to mw-backend
3. Wire Angular services (Api, Auth, I18n)
4. Build public site pages (Home, Practice Areas, Publications) from API
5. Build CMS pages (login, dashboard, CRUD editors)
6. Implement AiAgentService + AI Assist panel (with mock fallback)
7. Add motion/transitions; apply design system tokens throughout
8. `ng build --base-href /demos/solo-law/` → copy dist → verify in AppFrame
9. Push mw-backend, wait ~30s, verify live endpoints

---

## Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|
| WebGPU unavailable in Playwright headless | `navigator.gpu` check → mock mode; deploy-test asserts mock-fallback UI renders correctly (banner + mock output). For GPU-enabled local testing: `--headless=new --use-angle=vulkan --enable-features=Vulkan,WebGPU --disable-vulkan-surface --enable-unsafe-webgpu --ignore-gpu-blocklist` |
| Angular base-href 404s | Verify `<base href="/demos/solo-law/">` in dist/index.html post-build; test in AppFrame locally |
| WebLLM model first-load size (≥1GB) | Gate model download behind explicit "Load AI" button; show progress bar; never auto-download on CMS open |
| SQLite concurrent CMS writes | `PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL;` on DB init; connection-per-request OOP pattern |
| Multilingual schema drift | Schema locked above; seed covers both locales; SeedManager is idempotent |
| Angular build time | Keep component count tight; use OnPush change detection |

